                     /label="attP crossover (O region, 7-bp overlap)"
                     /parent="186_attP"
                     /note="Predicted 7-bp staggered-cut overlap (O region) at
                     which the 186 tyrosine integrase exchanges strands; lies
                     inside the attB-common core. GenBank NC_001317.1
                     misc_feature /note='attP; predicted crossover region with
                     attB'. Provisional: a GenBank prediction; the precise 7-bp
                     crossover has not been experimentally mapped for 186 in the
                     cited literature."
                     /db_xref="SO:0000057"
                     /citation=[1]
                     /citation=[6]
     protein_bind    191..220
                     /label="IHF site H2 (P' arm)"
                     /parent="186_attP"
                     /note="Candidate second IHF binding site on the P' (right)
                     arm, between the crossover core and the Apl operators (30
                     bp). GenBank NC_001317.1 annotates protein_bind here with
                     /bound_moiety=IHF and an /experiment qualifier. Provisional
                     and to be treated with caution: the closest characterised
                     relative (P2) is reported to carry only a single IHF site
                     in attP, so a second 186 IHF site would be 186-specific and
                     is not corroborated by an experimental 186 footprinting
                     study in the cited literature."
                     /db_xref="SO:0000057"
                     /citation=[5]
                     /citation=[6]
     protein_bind    209..256
                     /label="Apl operators (5x, P' arm)"
                     /parent="186_attP"
                     /note="Region containing five Apl operator sites. Apl is
                     the 186 recombination directionality factor (RDF; the 186
                     homolog of P2 Cox / HP1 Cox), a cooperatively-binding HTH
                     protein that recognises short direct-repeat operators
                     spaced about one helical turn apart, bends the DNA, and
                     directs excisive recombination while inhibiting
                     integration. GenBank NC_001317.1 protein_bind
                     /bound_moiety=Apl /note='five binding sites for Apl
                     excisionase at attP'. The 48-bp span is the region;
                     individual 6-bp operator coordinates within it are not
                     resolved from the annotation. Grounded by a 186-specific
                     quantitative binding study."
                     /db_xref="SO:0000057"
                     /citation=[4]
                     /citation=[6]
